{
    "level": "sentence",
    "abstract": [
        {
            "text": "The large data sample recorded with the Belle detector at the \u03a5(5S) energy provides a unique opportunity to study the poorly-known B 0 s meson. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Several analyses, made with a data sample representing an integrated luminosity of 23.6 fb \u22121 , are presented. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "We report the study of the large-signal",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "In addition, several results on B 0 s decays related to CP -violation studies are described. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Beside the non-flavor specific B 0 s \u2192 D \u2213 s K \u00b1 decay, the following CP -eigenstate decays are studied:",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        }
    ],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "Introduction",
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The Belle experiment [1], located at the interaction point of the KEK B factory [2], was designed for the study of B mesons 1 produced in e + e \u2212 annihilation at the \u03a5(4S) resonance ( \u221a s \u2248 10.58 GeV). ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 21,
                    "end": 24,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 80,
                    "end": 83,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "[2]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 4,
                    "end": 9,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Belle",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w0"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "After having recorded an unprecedented sample of \u223c 550 millions of BB pairs, the Belle collaboration started to record collisions at higher energies, opening the possibility to study the B 0 s meson. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 81,
                    "end": 86,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Belle",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "A significant theoretical effort on the B 0 s potential for studying CP violation in the Standard Model (SM) and beyond has taken place from the 90's [3]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 150,
                    "end": 153,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "[3]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The non-flavor specific decays such as B 0 s \u2192 D \u2213 s K \u00b1 are expected to be insensitive to new physics (NP); they can be used to measure the CKM angle \u03b3 [4] and help to resolve the ambiguity in the width difference in the B 0 s \u2212B 0 s system, \u2206\u0393 s [5]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 153,
                    "end": 156,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b4",
                    "text": "[4]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 248,
                    "end": 251,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b6",
                    "text": "[5]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The penguin-dominated decays B 0 s \u2192 K + K \u2212 are expected to be sensitive to NP [6] and the CKM angles \u03b2 and \u03b3 can be extracted by comparing its branching fraction (BF) with that of B 0 \u2192 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 [7]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 80,
                    "end": 83,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b7",
                    "text": "[6]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 196,
                    "end": 199,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b8",
                    "text": "[7]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Finally, the decays involving a b \u2192 ccs transition (the \"golden mode\" B 0",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": ", etc.",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": ") are probably the most promising, as the CP -violation effects in these modes are expected to be tiny in the SM [8]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 113,
                    "end": 116,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b9",
                    "text": "[8]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "A particular attention will be given to the B 0 s \u2192 D",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "modes because the width difference \u2206\u0393 CP s can be extracted from their total BF [9]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 80,
                    "end": 83,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b10",
                    "text": "[9]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Up to now, a data sample of integrated luminosity of L int = (23.6 \u00b1 0.3) fb \u22121 (out of a total of 120 fb \u22121 ) has been analyzed at the energy of the \u03a5(5S) resonance ( \u221a s \u2248 10.87 GeV). ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Since the \u03a5(5S) resonance is above the B 0 sB 0 s threshold, it was naturally expected that the B 0 s meson could be studied with \u03a5(5S) data as well as the B mesons are with \u03a5(4S) data. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The main advantage with respect to the hadron colliders is the better prospects of absolute 1 The notation \"B\" refers either to a B 0 or a B + . ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 92,
                    "end": 93,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Moreover, charge-conjugated states are implied everywhere. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "arXiv:1101.5052v1 [hep-ex] 26 Jan 2011 BF measurements. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "However, the abundance of B 0 s mesons in \u03a5(5S) hadronic events has to be precisely determined. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Above the e + e \u2212 \u2192 u\u016b, dd, ss, cc continuum events, the e + e \u2212 \u2192 bb process can produce different kinds of final states involving a pair of non-strange B mesons [10]   [11]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 163,
                    "end": 167,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b11",
                    "text": "[10]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 170,
                    "end": 174,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b12",
                    "text": "[11]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The B * and B * s mesons always decay by emission of a photon. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The total e + e \u2212 \u2192 bb cross section at the \u03a5(5S) energy was measured to be \u03c3 bb = (302 \u00b1 14) pb [12,13]  ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 97,
                    "end": 101,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b13",
                    "text": "[12,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 101,
                    "end": 104,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b14",
                    "text": "13]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": ". The signal coming from the dominant e + e \u2212 \u2192 B * sB * s production mode is extracted from a two-dimensional fit performed on the distribution of these two variables. The corresponding BF is then extracted using the total efficiency (including sub-decay BFs) determined with Monte-Carlo (MC) simulations, \u03b5B, and the number of B 0 s mesons produced via the e + e \u2212 \u2192 B * sB * [16]. These modes are expected to produce an abundant signal because of their relatively large predicted BFs [17] and their clean signatures: four charged tracks and up to two photons. The leading amplitude for the four",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 378,
                    "end": 382,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b17",
                    "text": "[16]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 487,
                    "end": 491,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b18",
                    "text": "[17]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "modes is a b \u2192 c tree diagram of order \u03bb 2 (in the Wolfenstein parametrization [18] of the CKM quark-mixing matrix [19]) with a spectator s quark. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 79,
                    "end": 83,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b20",
                    "text": "[18]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 115,
                    "end": 119,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b21",
                    "text": "[19]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Besides being interesting in their own right, such measurements, if precise enough, can be of high importance for the current and forthcoming hadron collider experiments. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "It was for example pointed out [20] that the search for the very rare decay B 0 s \u2192 \u00b5 + \u00b5 \u2212 will be systematically limited by the poor knowledge of B 0 s production, in case NP will enhance the decay probability by no more than a factor 3 above the SM expectation.",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 31,
                    "end": 35,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b23",
                    "text": "[20]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "In addition, polarization measurements of B decays have become of high interest since the observation of a surprisingly large transverse polarization in B \u2192 \u03c6K * decays by BaBar [21] and Belle [22]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 178,
                    "end": 182,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b24",
                    "text": "[21]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 193,
                    "end": 197,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b25",
                    "text": "[22]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 187,
                    "end": 192,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Belle",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The relative strengths of the longitudinal and transverse states can be measured with an angular analysis of the decay products. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "In the helicity basis, the expected ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Based on the ratio of the second and the zeroth Fox-Wolfram moments [23], R 2 , the continuum events are efficiently rejected by taking advantage of the difference between their event geometry (jet like, high R 2 ) and the signal event shape (spherical, low  Left:   ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 68,
                    "end": 72,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b26",
                    "text": "[23]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 52,
                    "end": 59,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Wolfram",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The different sources of systematic uncertainties affecting the measurements are identified and quoted as a second error. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Our results on the B 0 s decays are consistent with theoretical predictions [17] and with existing measurements (Table 1).",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 76,
                    "end": 80,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b18",
                    "text": "[17]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 112,
                    "end": 120,
                    "type": "table",
                    "ref_id": "tab_3",
                    "text": "(Table 1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Evidence for",
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": ", which is not flavour specific [16]. ",
            "section": "Evidence for",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 32,
                    "end": 36,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b17",
                    "text": "[16]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The analysis is performed in the same way as that of   ",
            "section": "Evidence for",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Observation of B",
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "We present our results for the",
            "section": "Observation of B",
            "paragraph_rank": 11,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "charmless decays [25]. ",
            "section": "Observation of B",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 17,
                    "end": 21,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b28",
                    "text": "[25]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The charged pion and kaon candidates are selected using charged tracks and identified with energy deposition, momentum and time-of-flight measurements. ",
            "section": "Observation of B",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The K 0",
            "section": "Observation of B",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "S",
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "candidates are reconstructed via the K 0 S \u2192 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 decay. ",
            "section": "S",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "A likelihood based on 16 modified Fox-Wolfram moments [26] is implemented to reduce the continuum, which is the main source of background.",
            "section": "S",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 54,
                    "end": 58,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b29",
                    "text": "[26]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 38,
                    "end": 45,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Wolfram",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w4"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "We do observe a 5.8\u03c3 excess of 24 \u00b1 6 events in the B * sB * s region for the B 0 s \u2192 K + K \u2212 mode (Fig. 4). ",
            "section": "S",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 99,
                    "end": 107,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "(Fig. 4)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The BF, B(B 0 s \u2192 K + K \u2212 ) = (3.8 +1.0 \u22120.9 (stat.) \u00b1 0.5(syst.) \u00b1 0.5(f s )) \u00d7 10 \u22125 , is derived. ",
            "section": "S",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "However, no significant signal is seen for the other modes. ",
            "section": "S",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "Including the systematic uncertainties, we set the following upper limits at 90% confidence level: Figure 4. ",
            "section": "S",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 99,
                    "end": 107,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Figure 4"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Distributions, similarly to Fig. 1, of the B 0 s \u2192 K + K \u2212 candidates and the fitted PDF as a solid blue curve. ",
            "section": "S",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 28,
                    "end": 34,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_2",
                    "text": "Fig. 1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The solid-red and the dotted-grey curves represent the signal and the continuum component of the PDF, respectively.",
            "section": "S",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The later is the first limit set for the B 0 s \u2192 K 0K0 mode. ",
            "section": "S",
            "paragraph_rank": 15,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "All the other values are compatible with the CDF results [27,28].",
            "section": "S",
            "paragraph_rank": 15,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 57,
                    "end": 61,
                    "type": "bibr",
