                    "text": "[27,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 61,
                    "end": 64,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b31",
                    "text": "28]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Study of",
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "980) Results about the first observation of B 0 s \u2192 J/\u03c8 \u03b7 and the first evidence for B 0 s \u2192 J/\u03c8 \u03b7 are reported [29]. ",
            "section": "Study of",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 6,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 112,
                    "end": 116,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b32",
                    "text": "[29]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The J/\u03c8 candidates are formed with oppositely-charged electron or muon pairs, while \u03b7 candidates are reconstructed via the \u03b7 \u2192 \u03b3\u03b3 and \u03b7 \u2192 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 \u03c0 0 modes. ",
            "section": "Study of",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "A mass (mass and vertex) constrained fit is then applied to the \u03b7 (J/\u03c8) candidates. ",
            "section": "Study of",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "The \u03b7 candidates are reconstructed via the \u03b7 \u2192 \u03b7 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 and \u03b7 \u2192 \u03c1 0 \u03b3 modes, while the \u03c1 0 candidates are selected from \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 pairs. ",
            "section": "Study of",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "If more than one candidate per event satisfies all the selection criteria, the one with the smallest fit residual is selected. ",
            "section": "Study of",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "The main background is the continuum, which is reduced by requiring R 2 < 0.4. ",
            "section": "Study of",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "The combined M bc and \u2206E distributions are presented in Figs. ",
            "section": "Study of",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "5 (B 0 s \u2192 J/\u03c8 \u03b7) and 6 (B 0 s \u2192 J/\u03c8 \u03b7 ). ",
            "section": "Study of",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "We obtain B(B 0 s \u2192 J/\u03c8 \u03b7) = (3.32 \u00b1 0.87(stat.) +0.32 \u22120.28 (syst.) \u00b1 0.42(f s )) \u00d7 10 \u22124 and B(B 0 s \u2192 J/\u03c8 \u03b7 ) = (3.1 \u00b1 1.2(stat.) +0. ",
            "section": "Study of",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "5 \u22120.6 (syst.) \u00b1 0.4(f s )) \u00d7 10 \u22124 . ",
            "section": "Study of",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 6,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 1,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b6",
                    "text": "5"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "This is, respectively, the first observation (7.3\u03c3) and the first evidence (3.8\u03c3) for these modes.  ",
            "section": "Study of",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "The B 0 s \u2192 J/\u03c8 f 0 (980) mode is especially interesting for the hadron-collider experiments because it has only four charged tracks in its final state. ",
            "section": "Study of",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "Recent calculations and measurements predict the ratio",
            "section": "Study of",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "to be \u2248 0.2 [30], 0.42 \u00b1 0.11 [31] or \u2248 0.24 [32], in agreement with other predictions from generalized QCD factorization [33]. ",
            "section": "Study of",
            "paragraph_rank": 17,
            "section_rank": 6,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 12,
                    "end": 16,
